text.tspan: Share of countries that have reported suicide data to the World Health
Causes of death are unreported in countries with poorly functioning vital registries. Suicide deaths are underreported in many
countries due to social stigma and cultural or legal concerns.
Note: Data refers to the years for which suicide data has been reported. Data from the most recent years is unavailable due to time lags
